  <summary date="2007-09-26T18:17:09Z" status="Introduced in House">Mail-In Ballot Tracking Act of 2007 - Amends the Help America Vote Act of 2002 to require each state and jurisdiction which transmits ballots by mail in the administration of a federal election to implement appropriate procedures to ensure that the ballots (except those of absent overseas and military voters) may be tracked.

Authorizes appropriations for requirements payments to states for FY2008.</summary>
